This paper deals with inverse reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of preferences and constraints on the learning process, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also mentions the potential applications of the research in human-robot interaction (cs.HC) and control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY, and cs.HC, in that order.
